Mobile Price Classification
¶

This dataset contains the sales data of mobile phones of various companies. Need to find out relation between various features of mobile phone and it's selling price.
In this problem we need to predict the price range considering the mmobile phone features.

Feature relations
¶

Battery power vs. Price range¶

In [213]:
df_dummy=df_train.copy()
In [214]:
def find_range(val):
    if val<=1000:
        return "low"
    elif val >1000 and val<=1500:
        return "Mid"
    elif val > 1500 :
        return "High"
In [215]:
df_dummy['battery_range']=df_dummy.battery_power.apply(find_range)
In [216]:
sns.countplot(data=df_dummy,x="battery_range",hue="price_range");
plt.legend(loc='center',bbox_to_anchor=(1.1, 0.5),title="Price range");
plt.title("Battery range vs Price range");

Battery power < 1000 considering as low. Having more number of phones in Price range 0.
Battery power 1000-1500 considering as Mid. Having all the price ranges in almost same count.
Battery power >1500 considering as High.having more number of phones in Price range 3.

In [217]:
sns.relplot(data=df_train,x="battery_power",y="talk_time");
plt.title("Battery power vs. Talktime");

There is no direct relation between battery power and talk time in the dataset.
There are mobiles with less battery power with more talk time.

In [218]:
sns.relplot(data=df_train,x="int_memory",y="price_range");
plt.title("Internal memory vs Price range");

Mobiles having all ranges of internal memory, lies in all price ranges.
There are mobiles with less memory having high price range and vice versa.

Training the model and Prediction
¶

In [219]:
df_input=df_train.copy()
categorical_cols=["fc","int_memory","n_cores","pc"]
for col in categorical_cols:
    print ("Creating categorical columns for ", col)
    df_input=pd.concat([df_input,pd.get_dummies(df_input[col],prefix=col)],axis=1)
    df_input.drop([col],axis=1,inplace=True)
    print ("Deleted original col ", col)

Creating categorical columns for  fc
Deleted original col  fc
Creating categorical columns for  int_memory
Deleted original col  int_memory
Creating categorical columns for  n_cores
Deleted original col  n_cores
Creating categorical columns for  pc
Deleted original col  pc
